Darn delicious is what I have to say. We tried to go there before, and we happened to visit on one of the two days they weren&#39;t open, so we&#39;ve been curious ever since. They are not open on Sundays or Monday (I&#39;m pretty sure), but we went last night, and I&#39;m glad we did! It&#39;s a bit pricey, but it&#39;s not overpriced for the quality you get. I had the meatloaf/green beans/mashed potato special, and my husband had the pork chop special with raspberry butter sauce. It&#39;s not as sweet as you&#39;d think, but I think my meatloaf was spectacular. It was moist and awesome. The pork chop was grilled, and it was so moist and perfect!! I also had a pineapple martini, which was super. Plan to spend probably $80 if both of you get one drink, more for more drinks. Everyone was very attentive, and the service was great!!! The ONLY bad thing is that it&#39;s kinda loud in there....we sat at a table towards the front near the bar, and there was a group a few feet away, and I kept having to ask my husband, &#34;huh, what?&#34; 

Sit towards the back, for real. 

Kudos Twin Forks

If I could write a negative or minus review I would!!!
I LOVE Asian food of all kinds, and I have experienced a lot of different culinary scenarios based on the geographical region I was experiencing it in but also in regards to the the region of China, Thailand, Vietnam, Japan, Philippines or rather any Asian country the cultural culinary heritage was coming from and in some instances I have had disappointing Asian food before but this was by far the WORST Chinese food I have EVEERR had in my life!!! With a capital yuck!!! First off I simply ordered egg rolls, crab cheese won tons and shrimp pad Thai with extra shrimp. The wontons were flat and squished with zero crab in them and hardly any cream cheese!!! The egg rolls were vegetable egg rolls and the vegetables were squishing out of them as though they were a few days old. The pad Thai was atrocious!!! Under done noodles and salmonella shrimp swimming in a greasy sauce-broth. I called to complain or rather warn them of their food poisoning issue and the manager said,&#34;we receive our fake crab won tons frozen and add cream cheese to fill them up&#34; &#34;you can bring your food back for a 25% refund on your next order&#34;
Well excuse me I will never order from there again and for all those that choose to eat there... Good luck with your bowls. I hope it works out for you! This place is an abomination!!!

This place served up one of the best tortas that I&#39;ve had in Denver. I walked into this restaurant, which is next to the liquor store on Colfax and Williams, and was greeted by Steve. Awesome attitude and he knew I hadn&#39;t been there before. Regulars come in and he knows exactly what they want. I let him know that I had been disappointed with the tortas I&#39;ve been getting lately. I told him that I drove all the way from near the airport just for this...boy was it worth it. I usually order to go, but something told me to have a seat and stick around for a few. 

I ordered a favorite, the carnitas torta and also a pollo torta (for hubby later...if it makes it that far!) with that, I got a chicken tamale and a cucumber lemonade. Wow, am I glad I traveled for this. Great service and food. I will be back! As Steve says, &#34;Not bad for a white boy!&#34;

Thanks for feeding the pregnant lady!

The first time I ordered here I ordered wings and a calzone and both were very good. I gave them a 3 because I though it was a nice little pizza joint that was pretty small inside but the food came out quick and was fairly cheap. The wings were better than Pizza Hut and the calzone, which was 3 toppings for $6, was more than filling enough and last me 2 meals. 

I closed my initial review out like this &#34;Will definitely be ordering from here again. Very good food at a good price. They get docked spot because there is hardly a place to sit inside purely a delivery/takeout joint.&#34; 

Well fast forward 2 years and I have finally made my way back. They have expanded the inside so there are plenty of places to sit. It was a mad house in there though, they had ingredients out in the front where you order and it was pretty clustered. I got the Hawaiian Deluxe pizza and pepperoni pizza rolls. The pizza was on point but the pizza rolls were kind of a let down. Overall, based on food, they would get a 4 but the set up, clutter, and the fact that they told me 15 min and I had to wait closer to 30 for my food was upsetting. I will give them another shot based on my first experience but hopefully they give me a good reason to keep coming back because I really want to like this place.

This is one of those places where apparently the &#39;sass&#39; is more important than actually paying attention to the guests. I walked in by myself for some breakfast, and was immediately greeted by three different women, all dressed for St Patrick&#39;s day. All three looked at me, and one asked &#39;How many?&#39;&#39;

I said &#39;Just myself, please.&#39;

&#39;Would you like to sit at the counter?&#39;

&#39;No thank you, I&#39;m not comfortable at the counter.&#39; I am extremely  tall and can&#39;t sit at counters easily.

She took this in and turned and walked away.

A few beats later, the second woman asked me the exact same questions, and also wandered off. Still I stood by the door.

The third woman then did THE EXACT SAME DANCE. &#39;How many?&#39;. &#39;Still one.&#39; &#39;Would you like to sit at the counter?&#39; &#39;STILL NO THANK YOU.&#39;

FINALLY, I get a seat. My order was screwed up: gristly steak, overcooked eggs, the coffee tasted burnt, and syrup didn&#39;t show up for my pancake until long after it went cold.

But they sure were efficient with my check!

I won&#39;t be back.
